just to get to the front door.

136
00:06:58.292 --> 00:07:01.629  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What are you looking at me for?
She does them in heels.

137
00:07:01.712 --> 00:07:04.966  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hey, keep my heels out of this.
-Why do you keep wearing them?

138
00:07:05.550 --> 00:07:06.676  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They're my trademark.

139
00:07:07.385 --> 00:07:08.928  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's like asking Frankie not to dress

140
00:07:09.011 --> 00:07:11.764  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
like she's going
on a granola run for her cult.

141
00:07:11.848 --> 00:07:13.141  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're putting yourself at more risk.

142
00:07:14.434 --> 00:07:15.351  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Really?

143
00:07:15.852 --> 00:07:16.853  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mm-hmm.

144
00:07:18.396 --> 00:07:20.857  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Fine. Fine. Maybe you're both right.

145
00:07:20.940 --> 00:07:25.403  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe this is the time to start
compromising for safety's sake.

146
00:07:26.070 --> 00:07:28.573  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You know, vanity be damned.

147
00:07:28.656 --> 00:07:30.700  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But I just--
I don't know what to do with them.

148
00:07:31.409 --> 00:07:33.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, here's something.

149
00:07:39.375 --> 00:07:41.085  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I think she's warming up to it.

150
00:07:45.214 --> 00:07:47.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Good morning, Joan-Margaret.

151
00:07:47.175 --> 00:07:48.301  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Morning, string bean.

152
00:07:49.552 --> 00:07:50.386  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
There.

153
00:07:52.221 --> 00:07:57.685  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Um... I think this is
your personal mail from home.

154
00:07:57.768 --> 00:08:01.230  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, for the love of Pete.
I'm sorry, wrong pile.

155
00:08:01.314 --> 00:08:05.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Not that I'm conducting
personal business on company time.

156
00:08:05.443 --> 00:08:06.819  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[both chuckling]

157
00:08:06.903 --> 00:08:11.491  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh! "Sol Days" in the office
are my favorite because of the laughs.

158
00:08:12.116 --> 00:08:13.034  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
And the work.

159
00:08:13.117 --> 00:08:17.246  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Work? Work, work.
Now I know where Bud gets it from.

160
00:08:17.330 --> 00:08:21.584  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think I had to make a few less notes
and corrections this week.

161
00:08:21.667 --> 00:08:23.211  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's a good sign.

162
00:08:25.838 --> 00:08:27.632  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Is he doing okay otherwise?

163
00:08:27.715 --> 00:08:29.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sol, let me tell you something.

164
00:08:30.343 --> 00:08:33.304  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
If you had told me
all those many years ago

165
00:08:33.387 --> 00:08:36.516  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that the little boy
who stuffed my Tic Tacs up his nose

166
00:08:36.599 --> 00:08:39.435  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
was gonna become my boss someday...

167
00:08:40.603 --> 00:08:41.979  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I would have believed you.

168
00:08:42.063 --> 00:08:44.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So... So, good?

169
00:08:45.483 --> 00:08:46.567  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So good.

170
00:08:46.651 --> 00:08:48.236  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay. Bye. Thank you.

171
00:08:49.028 --> 00:08:50.196  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Hey, Dad.

172
00:08:51.656 --> 00:08:54.158  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Whoa. [chuckles]

173
00:08:54.242 --> 00:08:56.577  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sorry, probably shouldn't kiss the boss.

174
00:08:56.661 --> 00:08:59.205  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or your 32-year-old man-son.

175
00:08:59.288 --> 00:09:01.749  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Can I get a copy of this, please?
When you get a chance.

176
00:09:01.832 --> 00:09:03.417  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Coming right up.
-Thank you.

177
00:09:03.501 --> 00:09:05.795  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
As soon as I freshen my Sanka.

178
00:09:07.672 --> 00:09:10.174  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sanka? Sanka?

179
00:09:11.008 --> 00:09:11.842  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sanka?

180
00:09:11.926 --> 00:09:14.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll have a-- I'll have a splash.
-We're good.

181
00:09:24.730 --> 00:09:26.524  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She cracks me up.

182
00:09:26.607 --> 00:09:28.484  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah, yep.

183
00:09:28.568 --> 00:09:31.028  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Too bad I have to let her go.

184
00:09:36.826 --> 00:09:38.160  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, there you are.

185
00:09:38.786 --> 00:09:40.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I, um... I need to talk to you.

186
00:09:41.414 --> 00:09:44.959  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, I cannot believe
you're wearing that thing.

187
00:09:45.960 --> 00:09:48.337  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, I know, but maybe Bud's right.

188
00:09:48.421 --> 00:09:51.048  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We wouldn't have had to do
all that crawling to the phone

189
00:09:51.132 --> 00:09:52.883  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
if I had one of these.

190
00:09:52.967 --> 00:09:55.136  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He's also right about the bears.

191
00:09:55.636 --> 00:09:57.638  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When do you ever go into the woods?

192
00:09:57.722 --> 00:10:00.308  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Bears are everywhere now.
There's a drought.

193
00:10:00.850 --> 00:10:03.436  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They're coming for our water
and picnic baskets.

194
00:10:03.519 --> 00:10:06.105  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
This wonderful article comes out,
and instead of

195
00:10:06.188 --> 00:10:08.899  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"Hey, congratulations,
let's pop out the champagne,"

196
00:10:08.983 --> 00:10:10.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
they give us Panic Alerts.

197
00:10:10.484 --> 00:10:12.028  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
They meant well.

198
00:10:12.528 --> 00:10:14.780  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But when everybody sees these
around our necks,

199
00:10:14.864 --> 00:10:19.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
they're going to look at us and say,
"Oh, poor old lady, she lives all alone.

200
00:10:19.327 --> 00:10:21.287  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She has medical conditions."

201
00:10:21.370 --> 00:10:23.080  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nobody's gonna say that.

202
00:10:23.164 --> 00:10:25.541  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Nobody thinks of us as "poor old ladies."

203
00:10:25.625 --> 00:10:27.710  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, yeah? What about your friends?

204
00:10:27.793 --> 00:10:29.295  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

205
00:10:29.378 --> 00:10:30.796  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Judy and Peter.

206
00:10:31.505 --> 00:10:35.051  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They called me "Poor Grace"
at your art show.

207
00:10:35.134 --> 00:10:39.347  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Maybe they said "pour Grace,"
like "Pour Grace another martini."

208
00:10:40.723 --> 00:10:41.932  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Or "Whore Grace."

209
00:10:42.016 --> 00:10:45.936  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I realize that's not a compliment,
but it's a lot better than "Poor Grace."

210
00:10:46.520 --> 00:10:47.647  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know what they meant.

211
00:10:47.730 --> 00:10:50.608  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I don't want people
to look at me that way.

212
00:10:50.691 --> 00:10:53.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I want them to look at me and say,

213
00:10:53.235 --> 00:10:56.322  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"There's the lady that
created a business in her 70s."

214
00:10:56.405 --> 00:10:57.782  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But we're doing that.

215
00:10:57.865 --> 00:10:59.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, but it's not happening.

216
00:10:59.659 --> 00:11:03.621  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Frankie, we have a great product,
but there's a lot we don't have.

217
00:11:03.704 --> 00:11:06.374  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We don't have capital,
infrastructure, distributors--

218
00:11:06.457 --> 00:11:09.293  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
The snacks, the mascot, the theme song...

219
00:11:09.377 --> 00:11:11.087  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I thought you were writing the theme song.

220
00:11:11.837 --> 00:11:13.172  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's gonna be late.

221
00:11:14.006 --> 00:11:15.132  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I have an idea.

222
00:11:15.216 --> 00:11:16.759  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're not gonna like it.

223
00:11:16.842 --> 00:11:18.052  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

224
00:11:19.345 --> 00:11:20.262  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay.

225
00:11:21.764 --> 00:11:24.183  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Out of respect for our friendship,

226
00:11:24.266 --> 00:11:27.770  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
would you let me tender my resignation
instead of just firing me?

227
00:11:29.146 --> 00:11:31.982  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Frankie, you're an equal partner.
You can't be fired.

228
00:11:32.066 --> 00:11:34.360  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Really?
-[chuckles]

229
00:11:34.443 --> 00:11:36.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Because I was under the impression
I could fire you.

230
00:11:36.904 --> 00:11:39.281  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Just... hear me out.

231
00:11:39.699 --> 00:11:43.494  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I got an e-mail this morning
from an old colleague, Mimi Becker.

232
00:11:43.577 --> 00:11:45.830  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She runs Purple Orchid.

233
00:11:46.539 --> 00:11:48.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Purple what?
-Oh, it's a big company

234
00:11:48.499 --> 00:11:52.711  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that specializes in adult romance
and intimacy products.

235
00:11:52.795 --> 00:11:55.589  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
They have all the resources in place
that we need.

236
00:11:56.173 --> 00:11:59.635  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So she would be just like our... partner?

237
00:12:00.219 --> 00:12:01.554  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
If she's interested, yes.

238
00:12:01.637 --> 00:12:04.098  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I did like it being just you and me.

239
00:12:04.682 --> 00:12:06.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, I know.

240
00:12:06.475 --> 00:12:07.643  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I do, too.

241
00:12:07.727 --> 00:12:10.521  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But this is the only way
I can think to make it work.

242
00:12:13.315 --> 00:12:14.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

243
00:12:14.817 --> 00:12:16.277  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay.

244
00:12:17.319 --> 00:12:18.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thanks.

245
00:12:21.782 --> 00:12:25.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
But only if you promise
to love me more than you love her.

246
00:12:25.661 --> 00:12:29.623  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-[chuckles]
-Tell me you love me. I love you.

247
00:12:29.707 --> 00:12:31.542  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me you love me.

248
00:12:32.126 --> 00:12:33.419  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Tell me you love--

249
00:12:33.502 --> 00:12:34.503  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're fired.

250
00:12:35.296 --> 00:12:38.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You cannot fire Joan-Margaret!

251
00:12:38.174 --> 00:12:39.383  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Not fire. Ease out.

252
00:12:39.467 --> 00:12:42.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's an institution here.
You can't just put her out to pasture.

253
00:12:42.970 --> 00:12:45.973  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dad, she's been in the pasture for years.
She's past the pasture!

254
00:12:46.056 --> 00:12:48.934  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I cannot believe my own son
is being so ageist.

255
00:12:49.768 --> 00:12:52.563  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Dad, look at the cup of Sanka
Joan-Margaret just brought me.

256
00:12:52.646 --> 00:12:54.148  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's how she makes it.

257
00:12:54.231 --> 00:12:55.399  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's water.

258
00:12:55.483 --> 00:12:58.152  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But she's been here since the beginning.

259
00:12:58.235 --> 00:13:00.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Of time! The other day,
she brought me a document

260
00:13:00.905 --> 00:13:04.575  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
with those tissues she keeps under
her sleeve stapled to the first page.

261
00:13:04.658 --> 00:13:06.285  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Those are her "Joan-Margarets."

262
00:13:06.368 --> 00:13:09.538  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Robert and I had fun
with all of her little slips.

263
00:13:09.622 --> 00:13:10.539  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How about this?

264
00:13:11.916 --> 00:13:15.127  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I asked her to go down to the coffee shop
and order me a BLT for lunch.

265
00:13:15.211 --> 00:13:16.545  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-And?
-Look.

266
00:13:19.965 --> 00:13:21.884  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's my BLT!

267
00:13:21.967 --> 00:13:23.344  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

268
00:13:23.427 --> 00:13:25.721  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You always have to order two, Bud.

269
00:13:25.805 --> 00:13:28.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
[scoffs] Really, Dad?
I have to accommodate her?

270
00:13:29.058 --> 00:13:30.518  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I need to let her go.

271
00:13:33.229 --> 00:13:35.689  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I can't agree with that.
-You know I'm right.

272
00:13:35.773 --> 00:13:37.566  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I can't agree with that, either.

273
00:13:37.650 --> 00:13:39.818  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Dad, this is my law firm now.

274
00:13:39.902 --> 00:13:43.030  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Don't I have the right
to hire the people that I want to hire?

275
00:13:43.113 --> 00:13:45.324  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who do their jobs the way I need them to?

276
00:13:45.407 --> 00:13:47.076  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
