00:21:09.559 --> 00:21:12.271  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's, uh... in the restroom.

418
00:21:12.354 --> 00:21:14.231  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, with my sister.

419
00:21:17.359 --> 00:21:20.821  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
So, how much more of a fee
is it for dinner?

420
00:21:20.904 --> 00:21:22.823  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Because I might spring for that, too.

421
00:21:23.907 --> 00:21:24.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's not paying.

422
00:21:25.033 --> 00:21:27.327  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh, does she have a coupon?

423
00:21:27.911 --> 00:21:29.579  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No. She's my wife.

424
00:21:33.458 --> 00:21:34.626  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Come on.

425
00:21:34.710 --> 00:21:39.298  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know it probably seems weird to you,
but she knows what I do.

426
00:21:39.798 --> 00:21:40.924  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's okay with it.

427
00:21:42.968 --> 00:21:44.636  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She's not so thrilled with the idea

428
00:21:44.720 --> 00:21:47.472  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
of actually meeting
one of my clients, however, so...

429
00:21:47.556 --> 00:21:50.392  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So, you do what you do with other women

430
00:21:50.475 --> 00:21:53.520  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and then you go home
and watch<i> Scandal</i> with her?

431
00:21:53.603 --> 00:21:56.481  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
We love<i> Scandal.</i>

432
00:21:57.149 --> 00:21:58.900  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
We're really looking forward
to next season.

433
00:22:02.446 --> 00:22:05.824  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look... I enjoy you.

434
00:22:07.659 --> 00:22:08.952  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But this is my job.

435
00:22:10.120 --> 00:22:12.998  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I need something more in my life.
Something that's real.

436
00:22:15.292 --> 00:22:16.585  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Don't you?

437
00:22:21.089 --> 00:22:23.091  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Perfect timing.
-[man] Your car, sir?

438
00:22:44.863 --> 00:22:46.364  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What happened?

439
00:22:48.784 --> 00:22:50.243  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Things got weird.

440
00:22:54.748 --> 00:22:56.792  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She had a hell of a run, Sol.

441
00:22:56.875 --> 00:22:59.544  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sometimes it's time to say goodbye.

442
00:22:59.628 --> 00:23:01.963  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I know, I know...

443
00:23:02.047 --> 00:23:06.468  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And, you know, retiring isn't
just about the person who's retiring.

444
00:23:06.551 --> 00:23:09.596  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's about giving way
to the natural order.

445
00:23:09.679 --> 00:23:13.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Giving other, younger people their chance.

446
00:23:13.183 --> 00:23:17.187  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I know your agenda, Mr. Adams.
Real subtle.

447
00:23:20.398 --> 00:23:22.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
She's just doing
her little "Joan-Margarets."

448
00:23:24.152 --> 00:23:25.612  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Forgetting things...

449
00:23:27.406 --> 00:23:29.449  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
maybe a bit more than usual.

450
00:23:29.533 --> 00:23:31.493  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yeah, but once the memory goes...

451
00:23:31.576 --> 00:23:33.453  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And you know, Sol,
this is not the first time

452
00:23:33.537 --> 00:23:36.832  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
that you and I have talked about it
being time for Joan-Margaret to retire.

453
00:23:36.915 --> 00:23:38.375  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
When did we talk about it?

454
00:23:38.458 --> 00:23:42.003  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
When we were on our way
to Butterfly Day at the Botanical Gardens.

455
00:23:42.087 --> 00:23:45.674  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Oh, yeah, you're right.
That was, like, two years ago.

456
00:23:45.757 --> 00:23:47.384  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Six years ago.

457
00:23:47.467 --> 00:23:48.677  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, it wasn't.

458
00:23:48.760 --> 00:23:50.220  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Yes, it was.

459
00:23:50.303 --> 00:23:53.598  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I remember after the butterflies,
I had a hot dog and a Fresca,

460
00:23:54.599 --> 00:23:58.019  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
which I ate while sitting
on a green bench near the lilac bushes.

461
00:23:58.103 --> 00:24:00.355  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Okay, stop showing off.

462
00:24:03.024 --> 00:24:04.359  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[sighs]

463
00:24:05.652 --> 00:24:07.696  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I feel terrible about this.

464
00:24:08.446 --> 00:24:09.698  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sol...

465
00:24:10.532 --> 00:24:13.785  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
"terrible" would be
Bud not getting the kind of support

466
00:24:13.869 --> 00:24:17.247  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and skilled help he deserves at his firm.

467
00:24:21.877 --> 00:24:24.671  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-You know what, you're right.
-Mm-hmm.

468
00:24:24.754 --> 00:24:27.424  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And I should be the one
to let her go, not Bud.

469
00:24:27.507 --> 00:24:29.342  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
She was our secretary first.

470
00:24:30.635 --> 00:24:31.845  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That's true.

471
00:24:32.929 --> 00:24:34.306  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You want me to come with you?

472
00:24:34.389 --> 00:24:36.641  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Though I'd rather not
because I'd probably cry.

473
00:24:36.725 --> 00:24:40.729  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
No one deserves to be fired
by someone in tiny buckle shoes.

474
00:24:40.812 --> 00:24:42.189  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[Robert] Mmm.

475
00:24:43.315 --> 00:24:45.233  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[guitar strumming softly]

476
00:24:45.317 --> 00:24:48.653  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ Oh, baby, oh, baby ♪</i>

477
00:24:48.737 --> 00:24:52.949  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ B-b-b-b-baby ♪</i>

478
00:24:53.033 --> 00:24:59.206  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
<i>♪ Oh, baby</i>
<i>I want you all up in my life ♪</i>

479
00:24:59.289 --> 00:25:01.583  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>♪ I want to make you mine-- ♪</i>

480
00:25:01.666 --> 00:25:04.002  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hi.
-Hi.

481
00:25:09.841 --> 00:25:11.218  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-Hey.
-Hi.

482
00:25:11.968 --> 00:25:13.637  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How did you do that?

483
00:25:13.720 --> 00:25:16.389  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can never get them all to sleep
at the same time. Never.

484
00:25:16.473 --> 00:25:19.017  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I played them some of my love songs.
-Ah.

485
00:25:19.100 --> 00:25:22.020  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Those songs I wrote
that I hoped would incite passion in women

486
00:25:22.103 --> 00:25:24.731  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
all over the world?
Put them right out.

487
00:25:25.815 --> 00:25:28.568  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I'd let you in to see them,
but if we were all in there together,

488
00:25:28.652 --> 00:25:30.320  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
we might run out of oxygen.

489
00:25:30.403 --> 00:25:31.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[chuckles]

490
00:25:35.158 --> 00:25:37.035  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It was mortifying!

491
00:25:37.118 --> 00:25:40.497  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
The EMTs rushed in
like it was an emergency.

492
00:25:40.580 --> 00:25:44.334  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I can't have them doing that
every time I don't answer the Panic Alert.

493
00:25:44.417 --> 00:25:46.378  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Mom, that's what they do.

494
00:25:46.461 --> 00:25:49.297  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I really don't like it.
And it may be my imagination,

495
00:25:49.381 --> 00:25:52.300  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
but the dispatcher strikes me
as a bit of a smart-ass.

496
00:25:52.384 --> 00:25:55.512  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
It's supposed to bring you peace of mind.
It's actually done that for me.

497
00:25:55.595 --> 00:25:59.224  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, I guess your mind was so at ease
that you didn't bother to call me

498
00:25:59.307 --> 00:26:00.684  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
since you gave me this thing.

499
00:26:01.268 --> 00:26:03.395  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
<i>Maybe these just provide a nice excuse</i>

500
00:26:03.478 --> 00:26:06.064  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
for kids to not check in
with their parents as much.

501
00:26:06.147 --> 00:26:08.358  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
That is not what's happening here.

502
00:26:08.441 --> 00:26:11.569  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I think you gave me
this contraption to keep you calm.

503
00:26:11.653 --> 00:26:14.781  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
You don't have to wear it if you
don't want to, Mom. I'll call you more.

504
00:26:14.864 --> 00:26:16.992  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
-I'll call you every day.
-Every day? Ugh.

505
00:26:17.075 --> 00:26:19.119  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I don't want to be tied to my phone.

506
00:26:19.202 --> 00:26:20.412  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Look, love ya.

507
00:26:28.336 --> 00:26:32.090  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Ultimately,
there comes a point when it's time

508
00:26:32.591 --> 00:26:36.011  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
to hand it over
to the leaders of tomorrow.

509
00:26:37.470 --> 00:26:39.556  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sol, this must be so hard for you.

510
00:26:39.639 --> 00:26:40.974  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It is.

511
00:26:41.057 --> 00:26:42.767  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I get it. I do.

512
00:26:42.851 --> 00:26:44.227  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Thank you.

513
00:26:44.311 --> 00:26:45.478  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You're welcome.

514
00:26:47.814 --> 00:26:49.441  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
So when are you leaving?

515
00:26:49.524 --> 00:26:51.401  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Probably around 5:00.

516
00:26:52.777 --> 00:26:55.530  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
No, I mean when are you retiring?

517
00:26:55.614 --> 00:26:57.282  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[stammers] I...

518
00:26:58.116 --> 00:26:59.534  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I...

519
00:27:00.201 --> 00:27:03.038  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm not retiring. Bud still needs me.

520
00:27:04.497 --> 00:27:07.125  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sol, can I show you something?

521
00:27:12.130 --> 00:27:15.133  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
These are Bud's notes on your notes.

522
00:27:15.216 --> 00:27:16.343  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What?

523
00:27:17.719 --> 00:27:21.348  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He goes back
and has to correct your corrections.

524
00:27:22.182 --> 00:27:24.809  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
He says you're changing
the way he wants it done

525
00:27:24.893 --> 00:27:28.480  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
and he feels like you double his workload
and slow him down.

526
00:27:31.358 --> 00:27:32.901  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Bugger off, Dad.

527
00:27:32.984 --> 00:27:34.235  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
He said that?

528
00:27:34.319 --> 00:27:37.697  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, that last bit
I may have heard only in my head.

529
00:27:39.616 --> 00:27:42.369  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I just wanted to make sure
he was successful.

530
00:27:42.452 --> 00:27:46.456  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, he's the one
who has to make sure he's successful.

531
00:27:48.208 --> 00:27:52.712  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And truthfully, he's not the only one
waiting for you to retire.

532
00:27:52.796 --> 00:27:55.757  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I've just been holding on for you, too.

533
00:27:56.508 --> 00:27:58.593  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Jesus, Sol, I've got to get out of here.

534
00:27:58.676 --> 00:28:00.595  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
You've been staying for me?

535
00:28:01.346 --> 00:28:05.975  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Well, and I might have
a lien or two against my house.

536
00:28:07.560 --> 00:28:09.771  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
But what are you waiting for?

537
00:28:10.563 --> 00:28:13.692  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
Robert wants you to retire,
I want you to retire,

538
00:28:14.359 --> 00:28:16.069  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
and Bud needs you to.

539
00:28:18.947 --> 00:28:21.950  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
How many times have I heard you
tell a client,

540
00:28:22.450 --> 00:28:25.995  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
"When it's time, it's time"?

541
00:28:29.874 --> 00:28:31.167  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I said that a lot.

542
00:28:34.045 --> 00:28:39.134  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
In fact, I think I just said that
to you a minute ago.

543
00:28:41.886 --> 00:28:42.887  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Sol...

544
00:28:45.807 --> 00:28:47.100  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
it's time.

545
00:29:10.290 --> 00:29:11.416  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
How'd it go?

546
00:29:13.710 --> 00:29:15.253  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I'm Joan-Margaret.

547
00:29:16.504 --> 00:29:18.047  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
What are you talking about?

548
00:29:19.466 --> 00:29:21.176  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
It's time for me, too.

549
00:29:23.470 --> 00:29:24.763  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
I did it.

550
00:29:30.769 --> 00:29:33.188  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
[whimpers] I'm retired.

551
00:29:38.026 --> 00:29:39.027  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Oh.

552
00:29:48.870 --> 00:29:52.165  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
I cannot believe
you're actually considering this.

553
00:29:52.248 --> 00:29:55.668  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
What? You heard Mimi,
this is a deal-breaker for her.

554
00:29:56.628 --> 00:29:59.255  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And from a business standpoint,
she's right.

555
00:29:59.339 --> 00:30:01.758  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
This is how you sell things.

556
00:30:01.841 --> 00:30:05.428  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:79.33% 
And this is a way for us to be bigger
than we ever could have imagined.

557
00:30:05.512 --> 00:30:07.263  position:50.00%,middle  align:middle size:80.00%  line:84.67% 
Who cares how big we are?

